<section>
  <h1>Hi, I'm Dhruv Jain.</h1>
  <p>
    <span class="marginnote">
      <img src="/assets/img/profile.jpg" alt="Dhruv Jain photo" class="profile-picture" />
    </span>
    I am a Research Engineer at <a href="https://olakrutrim.com/">Ola Krutrim</a>, working on post-training, evaluation,
    and deployment of large-scale language and speech models for production AI assistants. My work focuses on
    improving safety, retrieval and search, and tool orchestration in real-time systems, with an emphasis on
    multilingual and Indic AI. I built
    <a href="https://huggingface.co/datasets/krutrim-ai-labs/VoiceAgentBench">VoiceAgentBench</a>,
    the first multilingual benchmark for evaluating voice assistants on tool use, multi-turn planning, and adversarial safety.
  </p>
  <p>
    Previously, I worked as a Research Intern at MIDAS Lab, IIIT Delhi (with Prof. Rajiv Ratn Shah) on improving STEM reasoning in LLMs, and at NTU Speech Lab (with Prof. Chng Eng Siong) on ASR post-processing and domain adaptation. I completed my Bachelor’s degree in Electronics Engineering at IIT (BHU), Varanasi.
  </p>
